 `@{b}DC240Wizard@{ub}'
 @{b}=============@{ub}

 This is the english documentation. (Version 1.4)

 DC240Wizard is a small tool for the Kodak DC240. It provides basic download
 functionality to get the pictures out of your camera.

 The Kodak DC240 is a 3x zoom TTL AF digital camera with 1.3M pixel CCD. It
 takes pictures in "megapixel" resolution (1280x960 in 24 bit true color) or
 in VGA resolution (640x480 in 24 bit true color). The pictures will be
 saved as JPG files on a compact flash card. (There's a PCMCIA adaptor for
 the flashcards, but AmigaOS 3.1 fails to read the card) Fortunately, the
 pictures can be downloaded by the Amiga using a serial connection.


  @{b}Requirements:@{ub}
 @{b}===============@{ub}

   · An Amiga with Kickstart 2.0 (V37) or better
   · gtlayout.library V32 or better (included in the archive)
   · A 9pin/25pin serial port adapter (to connect the serial cable that is
     included in the DC240 package to the Amiga serial port)
   · A digital camera, compatible to the Kodak DC240


  @{b}Compatibility:@{ub}
 @{b}================@{ub}

 DC240Wizard was designed to connect to the Kodak DC240 only, but it may
 also work with compatible cameras. Here are the actual testing results:

   · @{b}DC240@{ub}: This is the reference camera. There are no known problems.
   · @{b}DC240i@{ub}: No reports, yet. (but should be compatible)
   · @{b}DC280@{ub}: No reports, yet. (but should be compatible)
   · @{b}DC5000@{ub}: No reports, yet. (according to Kodak, it is compatible)

 DC240Wizard should also work with the the following cameras:

   · @{b}DC200@{ub}: No reports, yet.
   · @{b}DC200+@{ub}: No reports, yet.
   · @{b}DC210@{ub}: No reports, yet.
   · @{b}DC210+@{ub}: No reports, yet.
   · @{b}DC215@{ub}: No reports, yet.

 If you have any problems with these cameras, you may have a look at
 DC210Wizard. This old version of DC240Wizard has been successfully tested
 with the DC200, DC200+, DC210, DC210+ and DC215.

 Other Kodak cameras like the DC120, DC220, DC260, DC265 or DC290 are 
 @{b}not @{ub}compatible to the DC240! (You have been warned!)

 If you want to have up to date testing results, take a look at the WWW
 support page (see below).


  @{b}Usage:@{ub}
 @{b}========@{ub}

 Connect your camera to the Amiga and start DC240Wizard by double clicking
 the program icon. DC240Wizard tries to establish the connection with the
 camera. When the connection is ready it tries to display the directory
 information of the inserted flashcard. On the DC240, the pictures should be
 in the /DCIM/100DC240 directory.

 You can configure the serial port with the @{b}DEVICE@{ub} tooltype.
 Default: DEVICE=serial.device/0/38400

 The DC240 supports 9600 bps, 19200 bps, 38400 bps, 57600 bps and 115200 bps.
 The internal Amiga serial port may not work with all values. (Tryout which
 value works best) Because of lacking hardware handshaking with the camera,
 it could be possible that other tasks are interfering the transfer between
 the Amiga and the camera. In this case, use another serial port with bigger
 buffers or do not start other tasks while transfering pictures.
 
 Press the @{b}Mark@{ub} button to (un)mark the actually highlighted picture in
 the listview gadget, press @{b}Swap@{ub} to (un)mark all entries and press @{b}Copy@{ub}
 to download the marked pictures.

 You can press @{b}Stop@{ub} to abort downloading. The retrieved files can be
 found in the @{i}Downloads@{ui} drawer. Use your favourite JPEG viewer (e.g.
 Visage or FJPeg) to display the images on your Amiga

 You can configure the download directory with the @{b}DRAWER@{ub} tooltype.
 Default: DRAWER=PROGDIR:downloads

 You can configure the delay after downloading a pictures from the camera with
 the @{b}SLEEPY@{ub} tooltype. (SLEEPY=20 means one second delay) Increase this
 value if DC240Wizard aborts multiple downloads after one file.
 Default: SLEEPY=10

 Do not forget to restart DC240Wizard if your camera looses power or if you
 have changed the flashcard!
 

  @{b}Future plans:@{ub}
 @{b}===============@{ub}

 · Set file date of downloaded pictures to picture date.
 · Upload border files. (or maybe pictures files if possible) 
 · Delete files.
 · Display thumbnails.
 · Create HTML index files.
   
 If you have more suggestions, let me know!


  @{b}History:@{ub}
 @{b}==========@{ub}

 @{b}V1.4:@{ub} [05.07.2000]
   · Bug fixed: Timing problems after sending commands. (Phew, tricky!)
 @{b}V1.3:@{ub} [04.02.2000]
   · Name changed to DC240Wizard. (the place where we belong)
   · Some commands were not supported by the DC240. . o O ( *@ż#! )
   · A break signal will be sent to speed up initialisation.
   · Command execution delay has been removed to speed up all actions.
 @{b}V1.2:@{ub} [05.05.1999]
   · Tooltype for download directory added.
   · Tooltype for delay between picture downloads added.
   · Swap button added.
   · Bug fixed: Picture index started at 0 (instead of 1)
 @{b}V1.1:@{ub} [25.07.1998]
   · Bug fixed: DC210Wizard could crash when connection to camera failed.
   · Bug fixed: DC210Wizard caused a small memory loss while connecting.
 @{b}V1.0:@{ub} [07.06.1998]
   · First public release.


